#rain module by yvain douard, yvain29@gmail.com  

This uses a counter and a modulo. Division by the modulo's factor is done to catch the correct count.
I recommend using it only to test hashes that have limited character sets.
Even though no work/researches have been made to carve the passwords according to the manufacturers of routers,
this will be less vain than running an incremental attack on a wpa password.

You can use -mask with gpu and cpu, but don't put more placeholders than needed te reach max speed.
